00117 short RNA_type_to_ID_code(StructRNA *type)

00122     if (RNA_struct_is_a(type, &RNA_Camera)) return ID_CA;
00123     if (RNA_struct_is_a(type, &RNA_Curve)) return ID_CU;
00124     if (RNA_struct_is_a(type, &RNA_GreasePencil)) return ID_GD;

00198 void rna_ID_fake_user_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)
00199 {
00200     ID *id = (ID*)ptr->data;
00201 
00202     if (value && !(id->flag & LIB_FAKEUSER)) {
00203         id->flag |= LIB_FAKEUSER;
00204         id_us_plus(id);
00205     }
00206     else if (!value && (id->flag & LIB_FAKEUSER)) {
00207         id->flag &= ~LIB_FAKEUSER;
00208         id_us_min(id);
00209     }
00210 }

00222 StructRNA *rna_PropertyGroup_register(Main *UNUSED(bmain), ReportList *reports, void *data, const char *identifier,
00223                                       StructValidateFunc validate, StructCallbackFunc UNUSED(call),
00224                                       StructFreeFunc UNUSED(free))
00225 {
00226     PointerRNA dummyptr;
00227 
00228     /* create dummy pointer */
00229     RNA_pointer_create(NULL, &RNA_PropertyGroup, NULL, &dummyptr);
00230 
00231     /* validate the python class */
00232     if (validate(&dummyptr, data, NULL) != 0)
00233         return NULL;
00234 
00235     /* note: it looks like there is no length limit on the srna id since its
00236      * just a char pointer, but take care here, also be careful that python
00237      * owns the string pointer which it could potentially free while blender
00238      * is running. */
00239     if (BLI_strnlen(identifier, MAX_IDPROP_NAME) == MAX_IDPROP_NAME) {
00240         BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR, "registering id property class: '%s' is too long, maximum length is "
00241                                         STRINGIFY(MAX_IDPROP_NAME), identifier);
00242         return NULL;
00243     }
00244 
00245     return RNA_def_struct(&BLENDER_RNA, identifier, "PropertyGroup");  /* XXX */
00246 }
